abstract: Two former prime ministers of Algeria were convicted and sentenced to prison Tuesday for corruption-related charges in a landmark trial, unleashing cheers of joy from pro-democracy activists who want an overhaul of the gas-rich country's political system.
snippet: Two former prime ministers of Algeria were convicted and sentenced to prison Tuesday for corruption-related charges in a landmark trial, unleashing cheers of joy from pro-democracy activists who want an overhaul of the gas-rich country's political...
lead_paragraph: ALGIERS, Algeria — Two former prime ministers of Algeria were convicted and sentenced to prison Tuesday for corruption-related charges in a landmark trial, unleashing cheers of joy from pro-democracy activists who want an overhaul of the gas-rich country's political system.
headline_main: Algerian Court Convicts 2 Ex-Prime Ministers of Corruption
headline_print_headline: Algerian Court Convicts 2 Ex-Prime Ministers of Corruption

abstract: Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad is hopeful of reaching an out-of-court settlement with Goldman Sachs over the 1MDB scandal soon, but he said compensation of "one point something billion" dollars offered by the bank was too small.
snippet: Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad is hopeful of reaching an out-of-court settlement with Goldman Sachs over the 1MDB scandal soon, but he said compensation of "one point something billion" dollars offered by the bank was too small.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad is hopeful of reaching an out-of-court settlement with Goldman Sachs over the 1MDB scandal soon, but he said compensation of "one point something billion" dollars offered by the bank was too small.
headline_main: Exclusive: Malaysia's Mahathir Hopeful of 1MDB Settlement With Goldman Soon
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: Malaysia's Mahathir Hopeful of 1MDB Settlement With Goldman Soon

abstract: Malaysia is considering selling stakes in energy giant Petronas to provinces where the company's oil and gas fields are, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad told Reuters on Tuesday, in a bid to raise funds for the debt-laden government.
snippet: Malaysia is considering selling stakes in energy giant Petronas to provinces where the company's oil and gas fields are, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad told Reuters on Tuesday, in a bid to raise funds for the debt-laden government.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysia is considering selling stakes in energy giant Petronas to provinces where the company's oil and gas fields are, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad told Reuters on Tuesday, in a bid to raise funds for the debt-laden government.
headline_main: Malaysia Considering Selling Stakes in Petronas to Provinces-Mahathir
headline_print_headline: Malaysia Considering Selling Stakes in Petronas to Provinces-Mahathir

abstract: Strikes against pension reforms shut schools and caused transport chaos around France on Tuesday, but the number of people taking to the streets dropped by more than half from last week, strengthening President Emmanuel Macron's hand.
snippet: Strikes against pension reforms shut schools and caused transport chaos around France on Tuesday, but the number of people taking to the streets dropped by more than half from last week, strengthening President Emmanuel Macron's hand.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Strikes against pension reforms shut schools and caused transport chaos around France on Tuesday, but the number of people taking to the streets dropped by more than half from last week, strengthening President Emmanuel Macron's hand.
headline_main: French Protesters Take to Streets Over Pension Reform but Numbers Dwindle
headline_print_headline: French Protesters Take to Streets Over Pension Reform but Numbers Dwindle

abstract: Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest serving premier, said on Tuesday it would be a good idea for the world's youngest prime minister, Finland's Sanna Marin, to ask "old people" for their advice.
snippet: Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest serving premier, said on Tuesday it would be a good idea for the world's youngest prime minister, Finland's Sanna Marin, to ask "old people" for their advice.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysia's Mahathir Mohamad, the world's oldest serving premier, said on Tuesday it would be a good idea for the world's youngest prime minister, Finland's Sanna Marin, to ask "old people" for their advice.
headline_main: Ask 'Old People' for Advice, World's Oldest PM Says to the Youngest
headline_print_headline: Ask 'Old People' for Advice, World's Oldest PM Says to the Youngest

abstract: European shares fell for a second day running on Tuesday, but a 6% jump in drugmaker Sanofi and a report that U.S. and Chinese officials are planning to delay tariffs set to kick in on Dec. 15 helped them end off session lows.
snippet: European shares fell for a second day running on Tuesday, but a 6% jump in drugmaker Sanofi and a report that U.S. and Chinese officials are planning to delay tariffs set to kick in on Dec. 15 helped them end off session lows.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - European shares fell for a second day running on Tuesday, but a 6% jump in drugmaker Sanofi and a report that U.S. and Chinese officials are planning to delay tariffs set to kick in on Dec. 15 helped them end off session lows.
headline_main: Possible Tariff Delay Lifts European Shares Off Session Lows
headline_print_headline: Possible Tariff Delay Lifts European Shares Off Session Lows

abstract: The confrontation exposed a deep rift among Democrats in a reliably blue state.
snippet: The confrontation exposed a deep rift among Democrats in a reliably blue state.
lead_paragraph: TRENTON, N.J. — The confrontation was brief but explosive, and it laid bare the deepening fault lines within the Democratic Party in one of America’s bluest states.

abstract: Chinese image providers Visual China Group and Imaginechina have temporarily suspended their website services after the country's internet regulator said they had committed violations and ordered them to make rectifications.
snippet: Chinese image providers Visual China Group and Imaginechina have temporarily suspended their website services after the country's internet regulator said they had committed violations and ordered them to make rectifications.
lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Chinese image providers Visual China Group and Imaginechina have temporarily suspended their website services after the country's internet regulator said they had committed violations and ordered them to make rectifications.
headline_main: Visual China Group, Imaginechina Suspend Websites After Chinese Regulator Finds Violations
headline_print_headline: Visual China Group, Imaginechina Suspend Websites After Chinese Regulator Finds Violations

abstract: Qatar's premier attended an annual Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) summit in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday, its highest representation since 2017, but there was no public mention of a 2-1/2 year boycott by its neighbors despite hints of a thaw.
snippet: Qatar's premier attended an annual Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) summit in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday, its highest representation since 2017, but there was no public mention of a 2-1/2 year boycott by its neighbors despite hints of a thaw.
lead_paragraph: RIYADH — Qatar's premier attended an annual Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) summit in Saudi Arabia on Tuesday, its highest representation since 2017, but there was no public mention of a 2-1/2 year boycott by its neighbors despite hints of a thaw.
headline_main: Qatari PM Attends Gulf Summit but No Mention of 2-1/2 Year Row
headline_print_headline: Qatari PM Attends Gulf Summit but No Mention of 2-1/2 Year Row

abstract: Hundreds of demonstrators closed down streets in northeastern India on Tuesday as part of an 11-hour shutdown in protest of legislation that would grant citizenship to persecuted Hindus and other religious minorities from Muslim-majority Pakistan, Bangladesh and Afghanistan who immigrated to the country illegally.
snippet: Hundreds of demonstrators closed down streets in northeastern India on Tuesday as part of an 11-hour shutdown in protest of legislation that would grant citizenship to persecuted Hindus and other religious minorities from Muslim-majority Pakistan,...
lead_paragraph: GAUHATI, India — Hundreds of demonstrators closed down streets in northeastern India on Tuesday as part of an 11-hour shutdown in protest of legislation that would grant citizenship to persecuted Hindus and other religious minorities from Muslim-majority Pakistan, Bangladesh and Afghanistan who immigrated to the country illegally.
headline_main: Indian Protesters Stage Shutdown Against Citizenship Bill
headline_print_headline: Indian Protesters Stage Shutdown Against Citizenship Bill
